esis as an epistemological challenge and redefines the analysis of literature and art as branches of an Historical Epistemology. Proceeding from the state of affairs in 20th century criticism and aesthetics (Benjamin, Adorno, Blumenberg, Merleau-Ponty), the epistemology of representation (Whitehead, Canguilhem, Bachelard, Rheinberger) is revised in, and with respect to critical consequences (Derrida, Marin, de Man, Agamben). From literary criticism and critical legal studies to the scenario of the life sciences, the essays collected here redirect the logic of research towards the epistemological grounds of an aesthetics underneath the hermeneutics of every day life.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aAesthetics, Moderny21st century. 0aArt and literature. 0aCriticism. 0aHermeneutics. 0aKnowledge, Theory of. 4aEmergence, memory. 4aEmergenz. 4aErinnerung. 4aHyperreflexivität. 4ahyper-reflexivity. 4aiconic difference. 4alatent vs. manifest. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831104849600 cprintz978311048258440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110486216423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110486216.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL